summary: An ordinance appropriating the sum of forty ($40.00) Dollars out of the General Fund of the City of Seattle, to pay the claim of Dagne A. Hanson for personal injuries received by her on the 26th day of August, 1914, while walking on the sidewalk located on the northerly side of Newton Street between Eloise Terrace and Westlake Boulevard, in the City of Seattle, and authorizing the drawing of a warrant therefor.
